HEADWORD: Fleshhood
<hw>Flesh"hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
condition of having a form of flesh; incarnation.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou, who hast thyself⟦br⟧
Endured this <qex>fleshhood</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fleshiness</ent>⟦br⟧
